# SwiftDrop Project Context

React Native + Expo managed workflow. Backend on Railway (Node/Express + Postgres). Firebase for Auth, RTDB, and FCM.

## Core file locations ‚Äî never recreate, always import

| What | Path |
|---|---|
| Theme / design tokens | `src/theme/theme.js` |
| Firebase (app, auth, database) | `src/services/firebaseConfig.js` |
| API client (base URL already set) | `src/apiClient.js` ‚Äî use `getJson`, `postJson`, `patchJson`, `deleteJson` |
| Auth store hook | `src/authStore.js` ‚Äî use `useAuthStore()` |
| Navigation ref | `src/navigationRef.js` |
| Firebase Admin (backend) | `swiftdrop/backend/src/services/firebaseAdmin.js` |
| Auth middleware (backend) | `swiftdrop/backend/src/middleware/auth.js` |
| Notification service (backend) | `swiftdrop/backend/src/services/notificationService.js` |

## Design system ‚Äî Obsidian + Volt

Always import from `../../theme/theme`. Never hardcode colours.

```js
theme.colors.obsidian      // #0A0A0F  ‚Äî primary dark background
theme.colors.volt          // #E8FF00  ‚Äî accent, CTAs on dark
theme.colors.signalGreen   // #4ADE80  ‚Äî driver online, success
theme.colors.offWhite      // #F5F5F0  ‚Äî light surface
theme.colors.background    // #FAFAFA
theme.colors.textLight     // #FFFFFF
theme.colors.textOnDark    // rgba(255,255,255,0.7)
theme.colors.textOnDarkMuted // rgba(255,255,255,0.4)
theme.components.ctaButton     // obsidian CTA style
theme.components.ctaButtonText
theme.components.accentButton  // volt CTA style (driver screens)
theme.components.input
```

## Navigation

- Stack navigation only ‚Äî `@react-navigation/stack`
- `@react-navigation/bottom-tabs` is NOT installed
- All screens registered in `src/navigation/RoleNavigator.js`
- Never use `navigation.navigate` to a screen not registered there

## Screen rules

- Use `SafeAreaView` from `react-native-safe-area-context` with `edges={['top']}`
- Wrap any screen with inputs in `KeyboardAvoidingView`
- Never use `position: fixed` or `position: absolute` for full-screen overlays ‚Äî use flex layout
- Bottom sheets: use `Modal` + `Animated` slide, not absolute positioning

## Address / map inputs

- Plain `TextInput` for address fields unless Google Maps autocomplete is explicitly requested
- `react-native-maps` is installed ‚Äî use `PROVIDER_GOOGLE` on Android
- `MapView` must have `style={{ flex: 1 }}` not a fixed height

## Photo upload

- `expo-image-picker` is installed
- Never call Cloudinary directly from frontend
- Upload via `POST /api/bookings/{bookingId}/upload-photo` as `multipart/form-data`

## Backend conventions

- Check existing files before creating: `firebaseAdmin.js`, `auth.js`, `notificationService.js`, `provinceService.js`
- Add new utils to `swiftdrop/backend/src/utils/`
- Wire new routes in `server.js` with a single `app.use()` line ‚Äî never touch other parts
- Use `verifyFirebaseToken` for driver-only routes, `auth` for routes that need a Postgres user row

## Build discipline ‚Äî run order

1. Write screen ‚Üí `expo start` ‚Üí confirm it renders without errors
2. Write backend ‚Üí deploy ‚Üí Postman test ‚Üí confirm response correct
3. Only move to next screen after current one is clean

## Bookings RTDB structure

```
jobOffers/{driverFirebaseUid}/   ‚Äî pending job offer for driver
driverActiveJob/{driverFirebaseUid}/  ‚Äî active job during delivery
bookings/{bookingId}/status      ‚Äî status string listened to by frontend
drivers/{driverFirebaseUid}/status   ‚Äî "online" | "busy" | "offline"
active_deliveries/{bookingId}/driver_location  ‚Äî live GPS from locationTracking.js
```
